<?xml version='1.0' standalone='yes'?>
<!DOCTYPE PLUGIN [
<!ENTITY name		"recycle.bin-next">
<!ENTITY plugin		"recycle.bin">
<!ENTITY author		"dlandon">
<!ENTITY version	"2026.07.24">
<!ENTITY launch		"Settings/RecycleBin">
<!ENTITY gitURL		"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/&author;/&name;/master">
<!ENTITY tgzURL		"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/&author;/&name;/v&version;">
<!ENTITY pluginURL	"&gitURL;/&name;.plg">
<!ENTITY supportURL	"https://github.com/dlandon/&name;/discussions/">
<!ENTITY MD5		"d29a3c9765c00f9b163f2835a68e450a">
]>

<PLUGIN	name="&plugin;"
		author="&author;"
		version="&version;"
		launch="&launch;"
		pluginURL="&pluginURL;"
		support="&supportURL;"
		icon="trash"
		min="6.12.0">

<CHANGES>
##&name;
###&version;
- Add: Advanced log filtering to the Deleted and Removed log pages.
- Add: Support for multiple comma-separated search terms and '*'/'?' wildcards.
- Add: Filter help text and a clear filter button.

###2026.07.13
- Fix: Reworked the Recycle Bin reload architecture so reload is now a true queued operation. All reload activity is performed once after the debounce timeout expires, eliminating synchronous work from reload requests.
- Fix: Do not complete a reload request if the Recycle Bin is stopped.
- Add: Recycle Bin now supports the Custom SMB Shares plugin. Custom SMB Shares automatically inherit the recycle bin of their parent Unraid user share, providing seamless recycle bin support without creating nested recycle bins.

###2026.06.12
- Fix: UD remote shares added to the recycle bin when "Legacy Mount Point" is enabled.  Remote shares don't get a recycle bin.
- Fix: During array shutdown, the heavy UD unmounting activity would get into a timing issue where a folder to monitor by inotify could go unavailable.  Inotify is restarted to fix this issue.
- Add: Additional start/stop/reload logging to recycle bin operations.

###2026.05.15
- Fix: Disk shares 'diskX' are not properly excluded from the Recycle Bin included shares when Disk Sharing is enabled.  The Recycle Bin works on user shares, not on disk shares.
- Fix: Trash size calculations stop when there is an incorrect share configuration instead of skipping the incorrect one.

###2026.05.10
- The 'recycle-delete' fails to delete from the CWD.
- The 'recycle-delete' needs to move individual files when a directory is deleted and not just the directory.

###2026.05.03
- Fix: Move inotify lock files.
- Fix: Reboot start up issue when var.ini is not available.
- Fix: Double start issue when array is first booted.
- Add: Cli delete 'recycle-delete' that will delete files to a share recycle bin from the command line.  It only works on shares that are enabled in the Recycle Bin.

###2026.03.27
- Notice: Initial release under the new license.
- Notice: Minimum Unraid version changed to 6.12.  There have been too many UI changes to maintain backwards compatibility beyond 6.12.
- Fix: Many page adjustments.
- Fix: Inotify not stopped properly when recycle bin is stopped.
- Fix: Start/Stop fixes to insure inotify is running.
- Fix: UI changes for Unraid 7.2 responsive design.
- Fix: Enable Unraid style tooltips.
- Fix: Restart issues when adding a UD device with a recycle bin.  Restart changed to 'Reload' to minimize Samba restarts.
- Fix: UD devices not handled properly in the recycle bin and trash sizes not updated timely.
- Fix: Improve inotify logging robustness.
- Fix: Change 'stopping_svcs' event to 'reload' the recycle bin, and not restart it to minimize Samba restarts.
- Fix: Improve inotify logging robustness and don't log trim on every inotify log entry.
- Fix: Adjust deleted files log page so buttons show on the bottom of the page.
- Fix: Setting on the recycle bin causing Samba to crash.
- Fix: Refactor trash size calculations for better performance and size calculations.
- Fix: Recycle bin crons stopped working.
- Fix: Inotify FIFO error terminating inotify.
- Fix: Inotify.recycle.activity script does not terminate properly when there is an inotify error.
- Fix: Recycle Bin not working properly on flash share.
- Fix: Natural sorting of the shares on the shares page.
- Fix: Rework fifo handling and check for enough watches in inotify script.
- Fix: Change the date format to not zero fill the day.
- Fix: Php error when trashsize file is missing.
- Fix: Trashsize incorrect at times and displayed when the recycle bin is not running.
- Fix: Show 'Flash (Boot Device)' when refering to the boot device on the Settings and Shares pages to be compatible with Unraid 7.3 internal boot.
- Rem: Unnecessary tooltips.
- Rem: The Samba '%P' parameter cannot be used in the recycle bin.  It isn't necessary and crashes Samba.
- Add: Show status 'Running' indicator on table header that would not show in Unraid 7.2.
- Add: Numeric inputs limited to numbers and min and max values added.
- Add: Fixed possible intermittent visibility of Unraid server in Windows Network by ensuring WSD (Web Services Discovery) rebind occurs after Samba config reload.
- Add: Notification when inotify terminates abnormally so it's clearer when the Recycle Bin logging stops working.  UI shows logging has stopped when it stops.
- Add: Don't 'Reload' the recycle bin when adding a UD Device share if UD Devices are disabled in the Recycle Bin.
- Add: Recycle Bin 'Reload' to adjust for devices being mounted by UD with a recycle bin or a share configuration change.  Restarting the Recycle Bin every time a UD device is added or a share is changed is thrashing the Recycle Bin and Samba.
- Add: Disable recycle bin if SMB sharing is disabled.
- Add: The 'appdata' and 'system' shares are now default excluded shares.
- Add: Don't start the recycle bin if the array is not running.
- Add: Share file delete log events are marked 'DELETE' and file deletes and purges from the .Recycle.Bin are marked 'REMOVE' in the log.
- Add: Sort share trash sizes numerically and not by human readable values to be properly table sorted.
- Add: Recycle Bin on exclusive shares and pool devices.
- Add: Show all shares with a Recycle Bin on the settings page.
- Add: Filter switch to show only today's log activity.
- Add: Troubleshooting tab to show possible Recycle Bin issues requiring action and allow user to do a test delete to confirm Recycle Bin operation.
- Add: Apply proper `.Recycle.Bin` permissions before shares are added to the Recycle Bin.  Incorrect permissions can cause the recycle bin to malfunction.
- Add: Limit scope of inotify to the .Recycle.Bin only so other file activity doesn't create log entries.
- Add: Debounce and delay on 'Reload' to prevent thrashing the Recycle Bin.  A 'Reload' event will occur if no other 'Reload' requests occur for 10 seconds.
- Add: Bake in OS and meta files to exclude rather that entering them on the settings page so the excluded files are only user files to exclude.
</CHANGES>

